  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n                        \u003cp\u003eA striking blend of futuristic design and advanced transit planning has emerged in Riyadh, where \u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/tag/Zaha-Hadid-architects/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eZaha Hadid Architects\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e has redefined public transportation with the \u003ca href=\"https://www.zaha-hadid.com/architecture/king-abdullah-financial-district-metro-station/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKing Abdullah Financial District (KAFD) Metro Station\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e. As part of the massive Riyadh Metro project, this architectural landmark plays a pivotal role in a transformative network set to reshape urban life in Saudi Arabia’s capital.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=573028\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-573028\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-1-810x608.jpg\" alt=\"Futuristic building with a wave-like roof design, illuminated at night. People are walking around the structure.\" width=\"810\" height=\"608\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-1-810x608.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-1-800x601.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-1-768x577.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-1.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Riyadh Metro system, developed by the Royal Commission for Riyadh City, stands as the globe’s longest automated rail network, stretching across more than 176 kilometers. With six lines and 85 stations, the system connects key destinations across the city, addressing growing urban demands with an environmentally conscious approach. At full capacity, the network is expected to accommodate up to 3.6 million passengers daily, helping to cut reliance on private vehicles and ease city-wide congestion.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=573030\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-573030\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-3-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"Modern architectural building with a curving design exterior. People walk along a wide pathway lined with trees and plants. Evening sky and streetlights are visible.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-3-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/03/KAFD-Metro-Station-Riyadh-Saudi-Arabia-Zaha-Hadid-3.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStrategically situated within the bustling KAFD, the station designed by ZHA functions as a central hub that links air travel, metro lines, and local monorail services. Its location enables fluid movement between Riyadh’s financial core and King Khalid International Airport, while also offering easy access to nearby bus connections and walkable public spaces.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=573031\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-573031\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e